<b>Posted On:</b> 8:20 p.m. 20/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: The Monopoly of Banded Mail will stop! This concerns ALL citizens of Norrath (lng txt)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/veeshan.cgi?read=110" TARGET=_self>Re: The Monopoly of Banded Mail will stop! This concerns ALL citizens of Norrath (lng txt)</A> (Tybolt)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>You are correct that this is not a true monopoly, however, it is very similar to the definition of an oligopoly. A small number of vendors control the supply of a good which is produced in a field with high barriers of entry. In this case the barrier is knowledge. The good news for Kiron and ourselves is that when these market conditions exist, it only takes one or two independents to break the price control of the oligopoly and prices crash back to a fair market value. Thanks Kiron, we appreciate your efforts.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
